---

## 1. Canonical Decision

`http://` is not identity.

`http://` is only the current browser transport adapter used to render sira/natt-os runtime surfaces in ordinary browsers.

Canonical layers:

- `anc://` = identity protocol
- `.sira` = sira root namespace / artifact layer
- `tools/thiên` = operator launcher
- `http://` = browser transport adapter
- SmartLink = resolver / coupling layer
- sira browser adapter = transport/render bridge

---

## 2. Boundary

Browser transport may:

- receive browser requests
- render HTML surfaces
- expose health/audit endpoints
- expose Mach HeyNa stream endpoints
- bridge `anc://` targets to browser-readable routes
- inject runtime audit bridge into HTML

Browser transport may not:

- define identity
- replace `anc://`
- replace `.sira`
- become canonical runtime truth
- bypass audit
- bypass SmartLink
- claim ownership over sira namespace

---

## 3. Current Routes

- `anc://core` -> `http://core.sira`
- `anc://audit` -> `http://audit.sira`
- `anc://tam` -> `http://tam.sira`
- `anc://nauion` -> `http://nauion.sira`
- `anc://apps` -> `http://apps.sira`
- `anc://mach` -> `http://mach.sira/mach/heyna`

---

## 4. Runtime Implementation

Current implementation:

- `tools/natt_domain_gateway.sira`

Current operator:

- `tools/thiên`

The implementation file may use HTTP internally, but documentation and command layer must describe it as Browser Transport Adapter, not identity.

---

## 5. Gate

Before any browser transport change:

- sira namespace validator pass
- sira browser adapter validator pass
- sira TS translation adapter validator pass
- `core.sira/api/health` pass
- commit and push
